**Category:** essay-draft lonergan aquinas aristotle animal-knowledge practical-knowledge verbum langer flay

**Abstract:**
Major essay combining material from August 1995 and October 1997 titled "Two kinds of knowledge in Aristotle's Metaphysics." Extensive analysis of Lonergan's Verbum on Aristotle-Aquinas epistemology. Includes quotations from Susan Langer on signs vs. symbols and Joseph Flay on predication. Develops distinction between experimentum in animals vs. humans, speculative vs. practical knowledge, and argues that "God" should be a proper name (Thou) not a common name (It with essence).

**AI Recommendation:** Central theoretical essay; precursor to 97-NOV-1 on God as proper name.

